====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
[[Image:FtThomasTower.jpg|200px|right|thumb|A nineteenth century [[water tower]]]]

# A very tall [[iron]]-framed structure, usually painted red and white, on which [[microwave]], [[radio]], [[satellite]], or other [[communication]] [[antenna]]s are installed; [[mast]].
# A similarly framed structure with a platform or enclosed area on top, used as a [[lookout]] for spotting fires, plane crashes, [[fugitive]]s, etc.
# A [[water tower]].
# A [[control tower]].
# Any very tall building or structure; [[skyscraper]].
#: {{ux|en|The [[wikipedia:Sears Tower|Sears '''Tower''']]}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} Any item, such as a computer case, that is usually higher than it is wide.
# {{lb|en|informal}} An [[interlocking tower]].
# {{lb|en|figurative}} A strong refuge; a defence.
#* {{RQ:KJV|Psalms|61|3}}
#*: Thou hast been a shelter for me, and a strong '''tower''' from the enemy.
# {{lb|en|historical}} A tall [[fashionable]] [[headdress]] worn in the time of King William III and Queen Anne.
#* {{RQ:Butler Hudibras}}
#*: Lay trains of amorous intrigues / In '''towers''', and curls, and periwigs.
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} High flight; elevation.
#*{{RQ:Milton Paradise Lost|11|passage=Nigh in her sight<br>The Bird of Jove, stoopt from his aerie '''tour''', <br>Two Birds of gayest plume before him drove.}}
# The sixteenth [[trump]] or Major Arcana card in many [[w:Tarot|Tarot]] decks, usually deemed an ill omen.
# {{lb|en|cartomancy}} The nineteenth [[Lenormand]] card, representing structure, bureaucracy, stability and loneliness.

